                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.24/560¾: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to The
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-03T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 3, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1937. For Johnson and Harriman from Hopkins.<note n="20" xml:id="d218fn20">Harry
                        L. Hopkins, Special Assistant to President Roosevelt, with primary
                        responsibility at this time for Lend-Lease affairs.</note> President
                    approves your accompanying British group to the Middle-east. Good luck.
                    [Hopkins.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
